  "raw_meta_yaml": "schema_version: 1\n\ncontext:\n  name: trivy\n  version: \"0.68.2\"\n\npackage:\n  name: ${{ name|lower }}\n  version: ${{ version }}\n\nsource:\n  - url: https://github.com/aquasecurity/${{ name }}/archive/v${{ version }}.tar.gz\n    sha256: dd8efd719709d09b41c98cdb9090654f8ed326f07b05ba7a4ffca4de2745aea3\n    target_directory: src\n  # csaf_distribution licenses\n  - url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/gocsaf/csaf/refs/heads/main/LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt\n    sha256: 074e6e32c86a4c0ef8b3ed25b721ca23aca83df277cd88106ef7177c354615ff\n    file_name: gocsaf-LICENSE\n  - url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/xi2/xz/refs/heads/master/LICENSE\n    sha256: 5c640056d513f276d56635af7a0bed81cb7eac02a31b6e56d40c416557a8d8ce\n    file_name: xi2-xz-LICENSE\n\nbuild:\n  number: 0\n  script:\n    - cd src/cmd/trivy\n    - if: unix\n      then:\n        - export GOEXPERIMENT=jsonv2\n        - go build -v -o $PREFIX/bin/trivy -ldflags=\"-s -w\"\n        - cp \"$(go list -m -f '{{.Dir}}' github.com/cyberphone/json-canonicalization)/LICENSE\" $SRC_DIR/json-canonicalization-LICENSE\n        - cp \"$(go list -m -f '{{.Dir}}' github.com/in-toto/in-toto-golang)/LICENSE\" $SRC_DIR/in-toto-golang-LICENSE\n      else:\n        - echo on\n        - set GOEXPERIMENT=jsonv2\n        - go build -v -o %LIBRARY_BIN%\\trivy.exe -ldflags=\"-s\"\n        - for /f %%I in ('go list -m -f \"{{.Dir}}\" github.com/cyberphone/json-canonicalization') do copy \"%%I\\LICENSE\" \"%SRC_DIR%\\json-canonicalization-LICENSE\"\n        - for /f %%I in ('go list -m -f \"{{.Dir}}\" github.com/in-toto/in-toto-golang') do copy \"%%I\\LICENSE\" \"%SRC_DIR%\\in-toto-golang-LICENSE\"\n    - go-licenses save . --save_path ../../../licenses --ignore github.com/aquasecurity/trivy --ignore github.com/csaf-poc/csaf_distribution --ignore modernc.org/mathutil --ignore github.com/gocsaf/csaf/v3/csaf --ignore github.com/gocsaf/csaf/v3/util --ignore github.com/xi2/xz --ignore github.com/cyberphone/json-canonicalization --ignore github.com/in-toto/in-toto-golang\n\nrequirements:\n  build:\n    - ${{ compiler('go-nocgo') }}\n    - go-licenses\n\ntests:\n  - script:\n      - trivy --help\n\nabout:\n  license: Apache-2.0\n  license_file:\n    - src/LICENSE\n    - gocsaf-LICENSE\n    - xi2-xz-LICENSE\n    - in-toto-golang-LICENSE\n    - json-canonicalization-LICENSE\n    - licenses/\n  summary: Trivy is a comprehensive and versatile security scanner. Trivy has scanners that look for security issues, and targets where it can find those issues.\n  homepage: https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy\n  documentation: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/\n\nextra:\n  recipe-maintainers:\n    - mediocretech\n    - fhoehle\n    - xhochy\n",
